<v Teacher>Let's speak informally.

00:09:25.740 --> 00:09:27.019
<v Teacher>I want to show you something.

00:09:27.019 --> 00:09:28.060
<v Teacher>So we're gonna use te

00:09:33.440 --> 00:09:33.920
<v Teacher>Good.

00:09:33.920 --> 00:09:36.320
<v Teacher>I want to show you something.

00:09:36.320 --> 00:09:38.560
<v Teacher>Quiero mostrarte algo.

00:09:38.560 --> 00:09:41.360
<v Teacher>So maybe you call somebody and you say, like, where are you?

00:09:41.360 --> 00:09:42.000
<v Teacher>I'm at home.

00:09:42.080 --> 00:09:43.680
<v Teacher>Okay, I want to pass by.

00:09:43.959 --> 00:09:45.320
<v Teacher>to show you something.

00:09:45.320 --> 00:09:49.560
<v Teacher>I want to pass by to show you something.

00:09:49.560 --> 00:09:54.839
<v Student>Quiero pasar a what was it I want to to show you something

00:09:56.100 --> 00:09:57.860
<v Student>Mostrarte algo.

00:09:57.860 --> 00:09:58.740
<v Teacher>Good.

00:09:58.740 --> 00:10:02.899
<v Teacher>Quiero pasar a because we had a verb of movement.

00:10:02.899 --> 00:10:04.500
<v Teacher>Mostrarte algo.

00:10:04.500 --> 00:10:07.459
<v Teacher>So if we're connecting a verb of movement to another verb.

00:10:07.180 --> 00:10:12.220
<v Teacher>we connect using this this extra a too quiero pasar a most

